com.avaya.csta.registration

Class EndpointRegistrationStateAdapter

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.avaya.csta.registration.EndpointRegistrationStateAdapter
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    EndpointRegistrationStateListener, java.util.EventListener

    public class EndpointRegistrationStateAdapter
extends java.lang.Object
implements EndpointRegistrationStateListener
    Implements a "do nothing" callback method for each EndpointRegistrationStateListener event type. To learn more about how to use a listener adapter, see Using Listeners in the Device, Media & Call Control (DMCC) API.
    Version:
    $Revision: 1.1 $

    • Method Detail

      • registrationEventNotify

        public void registrationEventNotify(EndpointRegisteredEvent event)
        Description copied from interface: EndpointRegistrationStateListener
        Callback method that is called when the endpoint is registered. This event occurs when the endpoint registers (for whatever reason). See the EndpointRegisteredEvent for more information.

        The device parameter that specifies the device that is registered is of type SubjectDeviceID so extracting the device ID is a two-step process: 

         SubjectDeviceID subjDeviceID = event.getDevice();
 DeviceID deviceID = subjDeviceID.getDeviceIdentifier();

        Specified by:
        registrationEventNotify in interface EndpointRegistrationStateListener

      • registrationEventNotify

        public void registrationEventNotify(EndpointUnregisteredEvent event)
        Description copied from interface: EndpointRegistrationStateListener
        Callback method that is called when the endpoint is unregistered from the switching function. This event occurs when the endpoint unregisters (for whatever reason). A reason for the unregistration will be present in the event. See the EndpointUnregisteredEvent for more information.

        The device parameter that specifies the device that is unregistered is of type SubjectDeviceID so extracting the device ID is a two-step process: 

         SubjectDeviceID subjDeviceID = event.getDevice();
 DeviceID deviceID = subjDeviceID.getDeviceIdentifier();

        Specified by:
        registrationEventNotify in interface EndpointRegistrationStateListener

      • registrationEventNotify

        public void registrationEventNotify(MonitorStop event)
        Description copied from interface: EndpointRegistrationStateListener
        Callback method that is called when the endpoint is no longer being monitored by the switching function. This event occurs when the Communication Manager switch fails or is restarted.

        Specified by:
        registrationEventNotify in interface EndpointRegistrationStateListener

      • terminated

        public void terminated()
        Description copied from interface: EndpointRegistrationStateListener
        A callback function which is automatically invoked on a listener previously added to a deviceID.
        Specified by:
